@node "System" "System Vorraussetzungen"

  To use dA cOOL iNSTALLER you need at least an Amiga (oh, can`t I use
  it on PeeZee ?) with harddisk and OS2.0. 

  dA cOOL iNSTALLER should be compatible up to A4000/060. It was successfully
  tested on A1200/030, A1200/040, A4000/040. I think there shouldn`t
  be any problems on higher machines. If there are, try to disable the
  caches, if my system patches are failing.  

  dA cOOL iNSTALLER needs also the reqtools.library (© by Niço François)
  in libs:. I`ve stored it in the dA cOOL iNSTALLER`s dir in libs/. Too
  bad that Niço quit the scene :-(

  Additionally you must have the Workbench installed on your harddisk and
  boot with it.

@endnode

@node "ques" "Installing a game/demo"

  It`s so easy.......

  I`ll explain it to your in three simple steps:

  1) Start dA cOOL iNSTALLER
  2) Select the destination path
  3) Insert a game or demo disk in DF0:

  THAT WAS IT! ALL IS DONE! Now start the game/demo and @{"register" link "register}.


  If you`re a registered user, these options appear
  somewhen in the installation procedure:

  1) Do you wanna use EmulateECS option? 
  2) Shall a drawer be created?
  3) if yes -> enter name

  EmulateECS degrades your computer to an unexpanded A500. You
  are now able to boot all your old games.

@endnode

@node "option" "Starting a game/demo"

  Simply doubleclick the icon.

  If the game doesn`t start, there`re several possibilities why,

  1) the game/demo uses a trackdisk loader, these games/demos can`t be installed yet (read history)
  2) the game/demo must be degraded (only @{"registered" link "register} version
  3) other error !?
  
@endnode

